10/ LTV to CAC ratio for us based saas is 3 but Indian context it can work even with 2.4 or 2.6
9/ Push the boundary. But there was psychological safety to fail (Which is very important to unlock the full potential of the sales team)
8/ Develop a growth mindset. The outcome of any problem is the result of the mindset you have. ‚ÄúWe are only constrained by our on mind‚Äù. THINK BIG. This is something to learn from Silicon Valley
7/ Be intentional about Culture. Advice from Jeff Bezos ‚ÄúI manage the culture‚Äù. At fresh desk ‚ÄúDon‚Äôt be a brilliant jerk‚Äù is one of the culture codes.

6/ companies ability to scale is more than that of individuals. Be mindful of titles you give to employees. Look for ability to learn when hiring. Read ‚ÄúGive away your Legos‚Äù https://t.co/x53ehhfgCv
5/ pick your battles. Optimise for speed over efficiency.
4/ Step by step. Change the world one milestone at a time. Focus on the next milestone.
3/ if you are not growing, take a look again into the business model. Founders know best and they have to figure this one themselves
2/ Business is simple. Don‚Äôt start with an idea. Start with a customer problem. Are we really clear about the problem? Once it is, it becomes clear how to build repeatable business model
